Ethics Training

Ethicsburg is available via the Internet to employees of participating Government agencies. It is a valuable resource tool that brings information on ethics and provides ethics training for Executive Branch employees. Use of this training, if approved by agency ethics officials, can be used to meet OGE annual training requirements for Confidential Financial Disclosure Report (OGE Form 450) filers. Employees who are not required to complete an annual financial disclosure report are not required to use this ethics training program, but they are invited to do so on a voluntary basis.

Ethicsburg is divided into separate areas. One area contains administrative and general information about the site and is situated under the “home” tab. You can always return to this page anytime by activating the “home” tab. The “training” tab is where we keep all of the training modules. We invite you to peruse one or more of the training modules during your visit. Users who login to the site using the access code you receive from your agency ethics official, will receive a Training certificate at the completion of training.

Ethicsburg welcomes and solicts customer feedback through an online comment form.

Federal agencies are invited to become partners with the Bureau of the Fiscal Service for training and information sharing. Ethicsburg links to a Government-wide community of interest in the ethics arena.
